  "texts": [
    "( 5)-( 9)).Algorithm 1: The bi-level optimization workflow.1 Input: Original graph T, relay model f θ, iterations {T 1, T 2 }.",
    "2 Output: Condensed graph S. 3 Initialise S and f θ.",
    "4 for t 1 = 1 to T 1 do ▷ Outer loop 5 Update S according to L T. 6 for t 2 = 1 to T 2 do ▷ Inner loop 7 Optimize f θ according to L S. 8 Return: Condensed graph S.The foundational principle of the optimization strategies posits that the performance of a model trained on the condensed data should align with that of a model trained on the original data.",
    "To this end, the losses for data T and S in relation to the parameter θ of the relay model are initially defined as:L T (θ) = ℓ (f θ (T), Y), L S (θ) = ℓ (f θ (S), Y ′), (3)where ℓ is the task-specific objective such as cross-entropy.Then the objective of GC can be formulated as the following bi-level problem:min S L T θ S s.t.",
    "θ S = arg min θ L S (θ)."
